<h2 id="further-reading">Further reading</h2>
<p>This module has used the following textbook as the primary source <a href="https://www.amazon.com/Essentials-Epidemiology-Public-Health-Aschengrau/dp/1284028917">Essentials of Epidemiology</a> and we reccomed it for in-depth reading on the subject. Other good textbooks on epidemiology include:</p>
<ul>
  <li><a href="https://www.amazon.com/Gordis-Epidemiology-David-Celentano-ScD/dp/0323552293">Gordis Epidemiology</a>: the definitive textbook on Epidemiology, now in its 6th edition.</li>
  <li><a href="https://www.amazon.com/Epidemiology-Matters-Introduction-Methodological-Foundations/dp/0199331243">Epidemiology Matters</a>: a new book that offers a different approach for learning based on competencies.</li>
  <li><a href="https://www.amazon.com/Applied-Epidemiology-Practice-Ross-Brownson/dp/0195187415">Applied Epidemiology</a>: a practical approach.</li>
</ul>

